{
  "stem": "9558.2",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 109,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So I took my mother in a hiding place.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 110,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Outside of Bochnia, outside of Wisnicz.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 110,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The place where she was there before.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 110,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the Polish chief of police was a very nice guy.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 111,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In Wisnicz.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 112,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 112,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I did remember his name.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 112,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He was killed by the Russians when the Russian came in.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 112,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he saved so many people.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 113,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "A neighbor went to the German police and told him that his neighbor is hiding a Jewish person.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 113,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And that was the second day of Kislev in 1943.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 113,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] '42? '43?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 113,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they came there to look for her.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 113,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But the guy, the Polish-- when the Germans-- the Germans never went without a Polish policeman.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 113,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So he used to serve them drinks and everything.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 113,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And he told his son, go and tell them there that we're going to come.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 113,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "He should-- whatever he is doing, whatever he does, he should clean up.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 114,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So they came there and looked around in the house, and they couldn't find anything.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 114,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And it was snow on the ground.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 114,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he had a bunker.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 114,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "In the back of his house was a forest, and he made a bunker for my mother.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 114,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they went out to look in the back door, and they saw footsteps.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 114,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And they went, and they took my mother and they send her with the transport.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 114,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 11 SECONDS]",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 115,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And [INAUDIBLE] after the war, I knew the day when they took, and they figured out this takes three days to go to the crematorium.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 115,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So I keep the [INAUDIBLE] the second day of Kislev.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 115,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] And after the whole families, with everybody, we had a gathering after 1945, and the rabbis decided that the 17-day [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 25
    }
  ],
